<!DOCTYPE HTML>
<html>
    <head>
        <% include ../partials/header.ejs %>
    </head>
    <body>
        <div class="container login">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-4 col-md-offset-4">
                    <h1>Please Login</h1>
                    <form action="/login/authentication" method="get">
                        <label class="loginForm" for="username">Username</label>
                        <input type="text" id="username" class="form-control loginForm" name="username">
                        <label class="loginForm" for="password">Password</label>
                        <input type="password" id="password" class="form-control loginForm" name="password">
                        <button type="submit" class="btn btn-light loginForm">Submit</button>
                    </form>
                    <p>This is a sample Node application deployed to Heroku. It's a reasonably simple app - but a good foundation for understanding how to get the most out of the Heroku platform.</p>

                </div>
            </div>
            
        </div>
    </body>
</html>
